---
export const prerender = true;
import AboutHeroImage from '../assets/blog-placeholder-about.jpg';
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About CaliDUIHelp"
	description="Learn what CaliDUIHelp is, who it's for, and the story behind the site."
	pubDate={new Date('April 24 2026')}
	heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
>
	<h2>What Is CaliDUIHelp?</h2>
	<p>
		CaliDUIHelp is a blog dedicated to covering what actually happens when someone gets a DUI in California — the court process, the DMV side, the penalties, and everything in between. Beyond just the legal steps, this site also covers real-world information people need to know and provides resources to help those going through the process.
	</p>
	<p>
		Whether you're trying to understand the system, prepare for what's ahead, or just educate yourself, this site breaks it all down in plain English — no legal jargon, no fluff.
	</p>

	<h2>Who Is This Site For?</h2>
	<p>
		CaliDUIHelp is for two types of people:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>People who want to learn more about DUIs</strong> — how the law works, what the consequences are, and what options exist.</li>
		<li><strong>People who just got a DUI</strong> — and need clear, straightforward information about what comes next and where to turn for help.</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Important Disclaimer</h2>
	<p>
		All content on CaliDUIHelp is for <strong>general informational purposes only</strong> and does not constitute legal advice. Every DUI case is different. If you have been arrested or charged with a DUI, you should consult a licensed California attorney who can advise you based on your specific situation.
	</p>

	<h2>About the Author</h2>
	<p>
		CaliDUIHelp is maintained by <strong>hackergood1</strong>, an independent content creator with a strong interest in making California's legal system more understandable for everyday people. This site was built to fill the gap between confusing legal documents and the real questions people have when they're facing a DUI.
	</p>
	<p>
		If you have questions, feedback, or topic suggestions, feel free to reach out through the site.
	</p>
</Layout>
